# A3S Box - Centralized Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env for base configuration
# Create .env.local for local overrides (takes precedence over .env)
#
# Loading order:
# 1. .env (base configuration, can be committed to git)
# 2. .env.local (local overrides, should NOT be committed to git)

# ============================================================================
# Workspace Configuration (REQUIRED)
# ============================================================================
# The directory where the agent can read/write files

A3S_WORKSPACE=/tmp/a3s-workspace

# Examples:
# - Use absolute path:
#   A3S_WORKSPACE=/Users/yourname/projects/a3s-workspace
#
# - Use relative path from src/ directory:
#   A3S_WORKSPACE=../examples/temp/a3s

# ============================================================================
# Server Configuration (OPTIONAL)
# ============================================================================
# LISTEN_ADDR=0.0.0.0:4088
# RUST_LOG=info

# ============================================================================
# LLM Configuration - NOT SUPPORTED
# ============================================================================
# The server does NOT read LLM configuration from environment variables.
# All LLM configuration (provider, model, API key, base URL) must be
# provided by clients via the Configure RPC call.
#
# This design ensures:
# - Better security (API keys not stored on server)
# - Flexibility (different sessions can use different LLM providers)
# - Stateless server (no default LLM configuration)
